Google translate is a free service that translates words,
phrases and entire web pages into more than 100 languages.
You probably already know it and you have used it many times
in your life.

In this tutorial, you will learn how to use Googletrans library
to translate text in Python. Googletrans is a free and
unlimited Python library that make unofficial Ajax calls
to Google Translate API in order to detect languages and
translate text.